descript.abstract: Worldwide runway locations polygon file. Data was derived from the Digital Aeronautical Fight Information File (DAFIF), a product of the National Imagery and Mapping Agency (NIMA) of the United States Department of Defense (DOD). The distribution of DAFIF is based on the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO) Aeronautical Information Regulation and Control (AIRAC) cycle of every 28 days.
descript.purpose: Intended to support transportation and logistics applications that require current information on airport locations.

procstep.procdesc:
Created by the Pacific Disaster Center, November 2002. Information derived from National Imagery and Mapping Agency (NIMA). This map service represents airport reference points from the NIMA Digital Aeronautical Flight Information File (AVDAFIF) published in ArcView shapefile format. Effective: 31 October 2002 to 27 November 2002.
Data was downloaded from the NIMA website (http://164.214.2.62/products/digitalaero/dafifindex.cfm) and reprojected to World Mercator with a central meridian of 150.
